                },
                "end": {
                    "month": 7,
                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2020
                }
            },
            "description": "\"Law and racism\" is a series of seminars on the interplay between Law and Racism in the Greek context for law students and recent graduates which Chryssa Mela planned, coordinated, and implemented in cooperation with Generation 2.0 for Rights, Equality & Diversity, Humanity in Action, and Anasa Cultural Center.\nThe purpose of this project was to sensitize and educate future advocates on racial issues, showcase that law is not neutral but excludes certain groups from its provisions and bring together professionals in the field and members of the communities of color with law students having the vision of creating a generation of legal professionals who are aware the racial/ethnic factor in decision making towards a more inclusive and diverse society. \nThis project was my Action Project as John Lewis Fellow at Humanity in Action",
